Overview 
Tonal is looking for a creative professional, passionate about health and fitness to help create new and innovative products. 
You will work on a diverse and growing creative and production team, focused on inventing a brand new form of production. We‚Äôre a ‚Äúfull-stack‚Äù video team with studio production, editors and producers all in-house. We focus on innovation, organization and extremely high quality, stretching what we‚Äôre doing creatively while being extremely detail-oriented along the way. 
What You Will Do 
Work closely with Director of Content to determine and define project objectives, scopes and deadlines Identify what resources are needed to successfully execute projects within the content department Establish timelines, track progress and identify any delays in projects before they occur Detailed planning and reporting of weekly and quarterly content releases Provide project updates to various stakeholders within the content team and cross-functionally Strategically and tactfully communicate next steps with thoughtful timelines to internal stakeholders On occasion, engage external vendors and manage those relationships for additional support on a project basis Perform post-mortems for each project so that we may refine our process from one to the next 
Who You Are 
2-5 years of experience in a project management role Experience working with creatives and talent Excellent project management skills, with the ability to manage multiple projects (video and/or TV a huge plus) simultaneously and prioritize workload Can work independently (self-starting) and within a team and have the ability to collaborate and take direction Ability to work under pressure and meet tight deadlines Very high attention-to-detail and organization Proven track record of developing and refining processes Experience using project management tools (Coda, Smartsheets, JIRA, etc.) 
